OL,3,CHome secretary announces plans to
OL,4,Coverhaul legal migration policy
OL,6,FCurrently, migrants who arrive on
OL,7,Fskilled worker visas and through
OL,8,Ffamily and humanitarian routes can
OL,9,Fapply for indefinite leave to remain
OL,10,Fafter five years.
OL,12,FBut those who contribute economically
OL,13,Fto the UK may soon be able to settle
OL,14,Fafter three years, with doctors and
OL,15,Fnurses in the NHS able to settle after
OL,16,Ffive.
OL,18,FMigrants could also only be eligible
OL,19,Ffor benefits and social housing once
OL,20,Fthey become British citizens, rather
OL,21,Fthan once they are settled.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
